Package berlin.hu.cep.connector

Class ZeebeConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ConnectorConfig
      • berlin.hu.cep.connector.ZeebeConfig
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ZeebeSinkConfig, ZeebeSourceConfig
    public abstract class ZeebeConfig
extends ConnectorConfig
    Abstract superclass for Zeebe configurations.

    ZeebeSinkConfig and ZeebeSourceConfig share a lot of common attributes and methods. They can be found in this abstract superclass.

    Author:
    Lukas Gehring, Leon Haussknecht, Maurice Lindner, Jost Hermann Triller, Stefan Zabka
    See Also:
    Kafka Connect connector for Zeebe

                   String name,
                   Boolean mongoDB_logging)
        Constructor of a ZeebeConfiguration. It sets all attrivutes which needs to be set by the constructors of the child classes.
        Parameters:
        connector_class - The name of the connectorclass where the Kafka Connect connector is implemented.
        name - The name of the connector.
        mongoDB_logging - Enables logging of all related events into a MongDB database.
